## 3. Naming Conventions

### Files & Directories

- Use `kebab-case` for all files and directories: `user-profile.tsx`, `auth-utils.ts`.
- Next.js special files use lowercase: `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, `route.ts`.
- Server Actions: `create-user.action.ts`
- Zod Schemas: `user.schema.ts`
- Types: `user.types.ts`
- Constants: `app.constants.ts`

### Variables & Functions

- `camelCase` for variables and functions: `getUserById`, `isLoading`.
- `PascalCase` for React components and TypeScript types/interfaces: `UserCard`, `UserProfile`.
- `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` for constants: `MAX_FILE_SIZE`, `API_BASE_URL`.
- Prefix boolean variables with `is`, `has`, `can`, `should`: `isLoading`, `hasError`.
- Prefix custom hooks with `use`: `useUserProfile`, `useDebounce`.
- Prefix server actions clearly: `createUser`, `updatePost`, `deleteComment`.
- Event handlers prefixed with `handle`: `handleSubmit`, `handleChange`.

### Components

- One component per file.
- File name must match the component name exactly: `UserCard.tsx` exports `UserCard`.
- Co-locate component styles and tests with the component if applicable.

