## 8. Tailwind CSS

- Use the `cn()` utility (from `clsx` + `tailwind-merge`) for conditional class merging — this is already set up by shadcn/ui in `lib/utils.ts`.

```ts
// lib/utils.ts
import { clsx, type ClassValue } from "clsx";
import { twMerge } from "tailwind-merge";

export function cn(...inputs: ClassValue[]) {
  return twMerge(clsx(inputs));
}
```

- Never use inline styles (`style={{}}`). Everything goes in Tailwind classes.
- Define design tokens (colors, spacing, fonts) in `tailwind.config.ts` — never hardcode hex values.
- Order Tailwind classes: layout → sizing → spacing → typography → colors → effects → responsive → states.
- Avoid arbitrary values (`[#fff]`, `[32px]`) — if needed more than once, add to config.
- Use `@layer components` in `globals.css` for repeated multi-class patterns only.
- shadcn/ui uses CSS variables for theming — always customize via `globals.css` CSS variables, not by overriding Tailwind config directly.

