## 10. Error Handling

- Use a consistent error boundary pattern (`error.tsx` at appropriate layout levels).
- Use the shadcn/ui `Alert` component to surface non-fatal errors inside UI.
- Log errors server-side with context; never expose stack traces to the client.
- Wrap async Server Component logic in try/catch and show meaningful fallbacks.
- Prefer `Result` patterns for server actions (return `{ success, data, error }` objects).

---

## 11. Performance

- Use `next/image` for all images — never use `<img>`.
- Use `next/font` for fonts — never load from a CDN in CSS.
- Use `next/link` for all internal navigation.
- Lazy load heavy Client Components with `dynamic(() => import(...), { ssr: false })`.
- Memoize expensive computations with `useMemo`; stable callbacks with `useCallback` (only when necessary).
- Prefer streaming with `Suspense` over loading skeletons manually; use shadcn/ui `Skeleton` for skeleton states.

---

## 12. Environment Variables

- Never commit `.env` — always commit `.env.example` with dummy values.
- Validate all env variables using Zod at startup (see `/lib/env.ts`).
- Only prefix browser-safe variables with `NEXT_PUBLIC_`.
- Group env vars by concern in `.env.example` with comments.

